postcontent:
Simple, it's the Noveske 11 inch rail it's awesome, below is the description from the noveske website. I'm asking 240.00 thank you. 

I live In Fort Worth.  

NOVESKE NSR HANDGUARD 
--Hard Coat Anodized Aluminum 
--Ultra Light and Robust Design 
--1913 Continuous Top Rail 
--Innovative Keymod Modular Direct Attachment System 
--Steel Barrel Nut 

Includes: 
--Handguard 
--Barrel Nut 
--Mounting Screws 
--T25 Wrench 
--Instructions 


BARREL NUT WEIGHT:3.1 oz. 

Made in USA 

The NSR handguard was designed with the goal of being the lightest and smallest free floating forend option to the M16 family of weapons. The width of the NSR handguard before accessories have been installed is only 1.48" The NSR handguard is available for sale as standard equipment on our rifles and upper assemblies, as well as a separate component for sale to the public. Available in 7", 9", 11", 13.5", and 16.7" lengths. 

The KeyMod inter-locking rail system is a collaboration between Vltor Weapon Systems and Noveske Rifleworks. Separately, both companies were in development of their own systems, but later realizing that both systems were similar, a standardization of the KeyMod system came to be. 

The KeyMod system offers a mounting platform for a variety of (future) accessories and components. The days of the Picatinny Rail (MIL-STD-1913) are numbered. The future of the direct mountable accessory is here and now. The KeyMod self-contained components/mounting hardware index and V-block onto the platform, achieving a secured and accurate hold to the system, while separate lugs take the recoil force off the fasteners. The pass through attachment method eliminates the need for loose screws and backing plates that can easily be lost, or difficult to install. Another advantage of the KeyMod system over the 1913 system is the direct attach eliminates the need for the 1913 system as a "middle Man" thereby reducing weight and accessory off-set from the center of the handguard.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Original HK91 -  Package Deal *** Price Lowered***
location: Anywhere in NWA, Arkansas, United States
postcontent:
This is an original HK91 in very good to excellent condition.  I believe I'm the second owner and the gun appeared to be a safe queen when I acquired it.  I've shot less than 200 rounds with it.  Finish wear IMHO is 95%+ with only typical claw mark wear and a small area around the optional ejection port buffer distracting from the finish.  Bore is bright and shiny and bolt gap measures .016" which is right in the middle of the normal range.  Date code is HH.

Included with the rifle is an original, new (never issued), Hensoldt Z-24 scope.  Hensoldt was the military arm of Zeiss and this scope is of the 3rd generation of optics used on this rifle.  These are becoming increasingly hard to find in the surplus market in new condition.  Comes with original claw mount as issued for it's time period.

Also included are 25 magazines (20 round) of steel or aluminum construction.  Some are new never issued while others show some usage.  Some are marked HK while the balance are stamped with HK contractor marks.  Buyer will also receive aftermarket owner manual and original sling.  Included in the spare parts survival kit that comes with this package are replacement rollers, extractor, springs, ect... to keep this battle rifle running well into the future.

Completing this package deal will be 1000 rounds of 7.62x51 brass case mil-surplus ammo manufactured by Hirtenberger in Austria. This is boxer primed, non-corrosive, 147 grain ball ammo packaged in original 20 round paper boxes.  Hirtenberger is considered one of the best mil-surplus manufacturers around.  

I prefer to not break up this package.  I would pull out the ammo if somebody wants to make an offer on this package without the ammo included.  I will not sell the scope or mount seperate as they stay with the rifle.

I will gladly meet anywhere in NWA.  NWA is defined as Fayetteville to Bentonville and anywhere in between.  There are two ways to contact me: 1) reply to this posting or
2) call me at REDACTED.  Please do not send text message.  I can answer all your questions in 10 minutes of actual conversation vs. hours or texting back and forth.  Text messages will be ignored.

Shipping to out of State FFL is available.  Add $150 for packaging material and shipping costs.  This option requires USPS money order.  I do not accept PayPal or similar services.

The only possible trade that would interest me is a piston driven (ie: adjustable gas port) AR type rifle in .308 (7.62x51) caliber and cash difference.  Prefer new but will consider like new offer.

Thanks for looking and I'll be glad to answer any legitimate question that was not answered in this post.

title: For Sale:  Need A Buyer For My Guns
postcontent:
I am a long term competitive shooter. No, not in a organized events sense, but against the harshest critic of all time... me, and sometimes my husband. For me, participating in organized events is about proving yourself to others or measuring your performance in comparison to others. Refining skills, progressively getting better with improved shooting techniques, finessing firearms and handloads... that can be done without the noise, distraction, fanfare, politics and expense of organized events.

While my hat remains off to the folks who do participate in formal events, I will also say that it doesn't take a professional competitor to appreciate and utilize the features of a good target rifle, like this Ruger M77 Mark II Target.

The Ruger M77 Mark II Target is a different type of Ruger. It's big. This one is 48" long in overall length with its 6.5 Creedmoor chambered, heavy contoured 28" barrel. The barrel has an 8" twist and is finished off with a recessed target crown. The matte gray stainless steel hardware is non-reflective and corrosion and bore erosion resistant. The barrel is full floating in the stock.

The laminated birch stock is wide in the forearm, flaring out from 1.75" at the floor plate to 2.50", making it ideal for shooting from a rest or other types of field support.
